      <para id="import-auto-id1375298"><title>Integrated Concepts</title></para>
      <para id="fs-id1571155">On its high power setting, a microwave oven produces 900 W of 2560 MHz microwaves. (a) How many photons per second is this? (b) How many photons are required to increase the temperature of a 0.500-kg mass of pasta by <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>45</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>0º</m:mn><m:mtext>C</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math>, assuming a specific heat of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>900 kcal/kg</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">⋅</m:mo><m:mtext>ºC</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math>? Neglect all other heat transfer. (c) How long must the microwave operator wait for their pasta to be ready?</para></problem></exercise>
